There are a few things that bug me here. (I remember reading this in chat, but I don't remember if I gave you any critique.) Most prominently:

1. drop casually in conversation all the time. It's common, but I always find it trite. It would be like Arby's employees talking to each other in hushed tones about how important it is that They Have The Meats. No matter how true or important, it would sound silly in any workforce after a while.

2. The containment procedures venture into insanity by the fourth tab. Which would be understandable if this ended in the end of the world as we know it, but it ends in the rest of the Council saying  spot in the world to protect something they weren't allowed to know existed.

I don't dislike it. It has the right scale for the 4000 contest, and I like the sweetness of the overall story, but too much of it rubs me the wrong way. No-vote for now.







